Ngwathe local municipality mayor Joey Mochela launched the high mast light project at Phiritona in Heilbron on Tuesday.Municipality s spokesperson Steve Naale said yesterday that the project is one of the mayor s success after his 100 days in office and they will continue work in ensuring that services are delivered to the people. The municipality will erect five more new high mast lights at the airport section. We making a follow up while delivering are our commitment to the people of Phiritona, Naale said while adding that residents complained about the level of darkness in the area during mayoral Imbizo.One of the airport residents Malerato Motaung said she was happy that mayor Mochela has delivered on one of the promises she made during the local municipal elections while she was on a door to door campaign. This project is an indication that our ANC government continues to keep its word on service delivery issuesaffecting our lives and most importantly our safety because without lights our streets are dark and criminals takeadvantage. Before local government elections, we spoke to our leaders about this matter and now they are here reporting back to us with visible developments, Motaung said.She further said the community was also happy about the mayor s commitment of rolling out dustbins distribution program in the area.When addressing Phiritona residents recently, Mochela said it was her job to make sure the municipality delivers on the promises they made to people, as they were her bosses. I am filled with happiness because the municipality has managed to provide services to our people.I am glad we managed to deliver this service as per the mandate of Operation Hlasela, Mochela said. The program started with Mayoral Imbizo in Ward 5 and our councillors invited the community to the sod turning with the technical team digging the first trench for the first high mast lighting, our residents were requested to safeguard these projects as they are their own benefit, Naale said.Sipho JackSNN2@thenewage.co.za